  "prompt": "Why does Draco Malfoy not have good relations with Harry Potter?",
  "response": "In the Harry Potter series, Draco Malfoy and Harry Potter have a poor relationship due to several reasons:\n\n1. Prejudice: Draco comes from a pure-blood wizard family that believes in blood superiority and looks down on muggle-born wizards. Harry, despite being a famous wizard, was raised by muggles and is sympathetic to people of all backgrounds.\n\n2. First Meeting: When they first meet in Diagon Alley and again on the Hogwarts Express, Draco attempts to befriend Harry, but Harry rejects his advances due to Draco's arrogant attitude.\n\n3. House Rivalry: They are sorted into different houses - Harry into Gryffindor and Draco into Slytherin - which traditionally have a competitive and antagonistic relationship.\n\n4. Personal Differences: Harry represents everything Draco is not - humble, brave, and kind - which makes Draco jealous and resentful.\n\n5. Family Background: Draco's family (particularly his father Lucius Malfoy) is aligned with Lord Voldemort, while Harry is the prophesied enemy of Voldemort, creating an inherent conflict.\n\nThese factors contribute to their long-standing animosity throughout their years at Hogwarts.",
